narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Topics surrounding sustainable land use planning
The different concepts and considerations that go into land use planning.
Basics of land use law, state/local policy and how understanding these foundations can help build more sustainable communities.

narratives.question_text: How well did the knowledge, skills, and insights gained in this class align with your expectations?
comments: I did feel like there was a more urban focus than rural. But, it was interesting to learn about the intricacies of many of the aspects of land use planning.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of the course and how could it be improved?
comments: Can complete lectures at your own pace

There are a lot of concepts that the course touches: the strength is that you can get a sense of how each topic relates to your direct interests; the weakness is that the course can only touch these topics and it is up to the student to go beyond the course.
Some of the lectures are dated.

narratives.question_text: What advice would you give to a student considering taking this class?
comments: Take this course if you are interesting in a cursory dive into land use planning. It will give you a taste of many aspects and you can take deeper dives from there.
Useful to audit. I perhaps would've gotten more out of taking it.
